
[1]enliven

   ENLI'VEN, v.t. enli'vn. [from life, live.] Literally, to give life.
   Hence,

   1. To give action or motion to; to make vigorous or active; to excite;
   as, fresh fuel enlivens a fire.

   2. To give spirit or vivacity to; to animate; to make sprightly. social
   mirth and good humor enliven company; they enliven the dull and gloomy.

   3. To make cheerful, gay or joyous.
